## Cost & Speed Reference

| Tier | Model | Relative Cost | Best For |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Claude Sonnet | $$$ | Quality, judgment, client output |
| 2 | Gemini Flash | $ | Volume generation, fast turnaround |
| 2 | DeepSeek V3 | $ | Good at HTML/CSS, cheaper than Flash |
| 3 | DeepSeek R1 | $$ | Reasoning-light mechanical tasks |
| 3 | Ollama (local) | Free | Offline, private, zero API cost |

---

## Decision Flowchart

```
Is the task client-facing or does it require full project context?
  → YES → Tier 1 (Claude Sonnet)

Is the task fully defined with no ambiguity?
  → NO  → Write a Tier 1 prompt first, then re-route
  → YES → Continue

Can it be specified in under 5 lines with a known output format?
  → YES → Tier 3 (DeepSeek R1 / Ollama)
  → NO  → Tier 2 (Gemini Flash / DeepSeek V3)
```

---

## Notes

- DeepSeek V3 handles low-to-mid HTML/CSS generation well and is significantly cheaper than Claude for volume work. Prefer it over Gemini Flash for markup-heavy tasks.
- Ollama local models are best for tasks where privacy matters (client data in context) or for offline work.
- This system applies per-task, not per-project. A single page build might hit all three tiers.
- Revisit model assignments every few months — the landscape moves fast.
